tests_documented_added_justification: Contributing guidelines (https://github.com/Wirecloud/wirecloud/blob/develop/docs/CONTRIBUTING.md) states tests should be provided.

warnings_fixed_justification: In general warnings are addressed. In some cases warnings are disabled for specific cases.
warnings_strict_justification: The settings for the warning tools are generally fairly strict.
know_secure_design_justification: Álvaro Arranz assumes overall responsibility for this along with the development team.
know_common_errors_justification: Álvaro Arranz assumes overall responsibility for this along with the development team. For a discussion of security requirements, common types of security vulnerabilities, and how this application counters those common kinds of vulnerabilities, see: https://github.com/Wirecloud/wirecloud/blob/develop/doc/security.md
crypto_published_justification:
WireCloud delegates authentication to other components such as KeyRock, Keycloak, WSO2 Identity server.... These security components use strong encryption protocols and algorithms to store salted hashed iterated passwords and for storing user information and https+standard crypto protocols to communicate with users.

WireCloud can also be used for authenticating users, in this case WireCloud uses Django's utils for storing passwords in a secure way. WireCloud also stores some sensitive data when configuring the access to third-party services. In this case WireCloud is using AES encryption to store it on hard disk. In any case, that sensitive information can only be used by the WireCloud's proxy service through secure channels and cannot be read back to the browser.

Communication with users takes place using https+standard crypto protocols when correctly deployed.
crypto_call_justification: WireCloud is relaying on the already available cryptography tools and packages for managing data encryption.
crypto_floss_justification: All required functionality is implemented using FLOSS, including cryptography.
crypto_keylength_justification:
WireCloud is using AES-256 for sensitive data.

Exact key lengths for the other aspects depends on the used component, but Django, KeyRock, KeyCloak, ... are currently using enough key lengths.
crypto_working_justification: WireCloud itself does not uses broken cryptographic algorithms. User can configure other services using broken protocols, WireCloud emphasize not to use them and to configure services using proper configurations.
crypto_pfs_justification: WireCloud itself is not using protocols requiring perfect forward secrecy, except for accessing HTTPS configured to do so. WireCloud HTTPS configuration should be configured to use perfect forward secrecy. WireCloud points to documentation explaining how to enable Perfect Forward Secrecy.
crypto_password_storage_justification: Using Django tools that follows those criteria. OAuth2 tokens are stored in plain as provided by the auth server (server can provide encrypted tokens), but are short lived.
delivery_mitm_justification: Documentation states how to configure WireCloud to listen on https. Also, WireClouds connects to other services using https.
vulnerabilities_fixed_60_days_justificat: No such vulnerabilities at this time.
vulnerabilities_critical_fixed_justifica: No such vulnerabilities at this time.
static_analysis_justification: As noted in https://github.com/Wirecloud/wirecloud/blob/develop/docs/CONTRIBUTING.md, JavaScript client-side code is analyzed using ESLint. Python code is analysed using flake8. These analysis tools are used in local development, as well as the continuous integration server running on Travis CI
static_analysis_common_vulnerabilities_j: ESLint specifically looks for common vulnerabilities in JavaScript applications.
static_analysis_fixed_justification: This is vacuously true, since we've had no reports of vulnerabilities that apply to a deployed system.
static_analysis_often_justification: All commits to GitHub are run through Travis, which performs a number of static analysis checks (ESLint, flake8, ...).
dynamic_analysis_justification: Dynamic code analysis has not been applied
dynamic_analysis_unsafe_justification: WireCloud uses languages that are not affected by this.
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: Instead of embedding run-time assertions, there are many external tests with assertions that are checked during automated testing.
dynamic_analysis_fixed_justification: WireCloud is not running dynamic code analysis and thus have not found any vulnerabilities in this way.
crypto_weaknesses_justification: WireCloud does not depend on any algorithms or mode with known serious weaknesses at the present time.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: WireCloud is currently using Travis CI.
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests.
no_leaked_credentials_justification: No valid private credentials are leaked. Usernames and Passwords may be entered using Docker secrets and ENVs
hardened_site_justification: // X-Content-Type-Options was not set to "nosniff".
implementation_languages: JavaScript, Python, SCSS, API Blueprint, Shell, Dockerfile

name: Monado
description: Monado is an open source XR runtime delivering immersive experiences such as VR and AR on mobile, PC/desktop, and any other device. Monado aims to be a complete and conforming implementation of the OpenXR API made by Khronos.
contribution_justification: Non-trivial description of contributions at https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/monado/monado/-/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md
contribution_requirements_justification: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/monado/monado/-/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md references code style (clang-format), suggests an issue before a large change, etc.
license_location_justification:
LICENSE file: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/monado/monado/-/blob/master/LICENSE
All license texts are in: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/monado/monado/-/tree/master/LICENSES
Each source file is either tagged with an SPDX-License-Identifier (or in an adjacent .license file), or handled in the REUSE-style "DEP5" file: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/monado/monado/-/blob/master/.reuse/dep5
floss_license_justification: All software in the project is FLOSS: code written explicitly for the project is BSL-1.0, while some other permissive licenses are also permitted in the codebase. We generally follow the REUSE project specifications https://reuse.software and will enable that check in CI once we are fully compliant. The BSL-1.0 license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
floss_license_osi_justification: The list of used licenses is: Apache-2.0, BSD-2-Clause, BSD-3-Clause, BSL-1.0, CC-BY-4.0, CC0-1.0, LicenseRef-Khronos-Free-Use-License-for-Software-and-Documentation, MIT.  The "LicenseRef-Khronos-Free-Use-License-for-Software-and-Documentation" is a variant of MIT used historically by the Khronos Group for some of their header files: it is only used in Monado for vendored dependencies. The BSL-1.0 license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
documentation_basics_justification: https://monado.freedesktop.org is the main documentation homepage.
documentation_interface_justification:
The external interface (API) is OpenXR 1.0: the specification https://www.khronos.org/registry/OpenXR/specs/1.0/html/xrspec.html is linked from the main documentation page.
Internal interfaces are documented in Doxygen, with generated output continuously updated by CI at https://monado.pages.freedesktop.org/monado/
repo_public_justification: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/monado/monado
repo_distributed_justification: Git is used.
version_unique_justification: Versioned tags are used. `git describe` is used to generate version names for intermediate commits.
version_semver_justification: Currently in the 0.x release series. External API is externally determined by a standards org, making semver less valuable.
release_notes_justification: Human-readable changelog updated at releases: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/monado/monado/-/blob/master/doc/CHANGELOG.md . Changelog built over time using Proclamation and changelog fragments added by contributions: "live" in progress changelog updated by CI at https://monado.pages.freedesktop.org/monado/md__c_h_a_n_g_e_l_o_g.html
enhancement_responses_justification: Most enhancement requests are in fact TODO items from a project lead.
vulnerability_report_process_justificati: GitLab issues https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/monado/monado/-/issues or project contacts in README.
vulnerability_report_private_justificati:
Private issues submitted over https: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/monado/monado/-/issues
Adding documentation on OpenPGP email to a project lead.
build_common_tools_justification: CMake is the primary build system. Meson is offered as an alternative. Android builds are done using Gradle, which builds Java/Kotlin code and invokes the CMake build for native code.
build_floss_tools_justification: This is true on Linux. On Android, no proprietary dependencies are used, but the Android Studio build from Google is used as the build environment.
test_justification:
Some functionality is tested through internally-maintained tests: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/monado/monado/-/tree/master/tests

Conformance with API specification is tested through a conformance test suite (with automated and interactive parts): https://github.com/KhronosGroup/OpenXR-CTS
test_invocation_justification: The internal tests are run through ctest, so `make test`, etc.
test_most_justification: Internal unit tests do not cover most of the code base. Conformance tests test a substantial portion of the codebase.
test_policy_justification: New API functionality is tested by the CTS, but no internal test policy exists.
delivery_unsigned_justification: No cryptographic hashes are used nor are any data retrieved over http by the software.
vulnerabilities_fixed_60_days_justificat: No reported or publicly known vulnerabilities.
vulnerabilities_critical_fixed_justifica: No reported or publicly known vulnerabilities.
static_analysis_justification: Clang static analyzer and Coverity have been used from time to time, but there is no explicit policy of doing so before a release.
static_analysis_common_vulnerabilities_j: Both Clang static analysis and Coverity look for common vulnerabilities.
static_analysis_fixed_justification: Have not verified this, though I think it is true.
dynamic_analysis_justification: Unsure what fuzzer would be appropriate for this application. Sanitizers and Valgrind are used from time to time.
dynamic_analysis_unsafe_justification: Unsure what fuzzer would be appropriate for this application.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: CI is used, including multiple-platform builds, though only the internal tests are run in it.
discussion_justification:
Provided by GitLab service, hosted by freedesktop.org: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/monado/monado

Additionally, Discord and IRC are available, but not explicitly archived.
hardened_site_justification: // X-Content-Type-Options was not set to "nosniff".
implementation_languages: C, C++, CMake, Python, Java, Kotlin, Markdown, Sh
